## 1. Verdict: **Conditional**

The taxonomy, invariant, and Definition-era corrections are substantively correct and verified against code (file paths, hard-coded fallbacks, timeout constants, dead adapter wiring all check out). But one edit corrupts a historical evidence record, and one edit inconsistently erases a historical product name in the same file where a sibling edit got it right. Fix both before treating this docs pass as settled authority.

## 2. Blocking Issues

| File | Issue | Severity | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| `docs/assessment-overall-state-2026-07-07.md:149` | The live-probe evidence line `` `/api/platform/retrieval/search` returns zero results for terms that verifiably exist in Texture documents ("choir", "world wire")`` was rewritten from `"universal wire"`. This is not descriptive prose — it's the literal search string used in an actual `curl`/CLI probe against `choir.news` on 2026-07-07, a day before "World Wire" existed as a name. Rewriting a quoted test input falsifies the evidence record (violates item 7 and the doc's own `Status: assessment / evidence` header — see AGENTS.md "Problem Documentation First" spirit on evidence fidelity). | Blocking | Revert to `"universal wire"` (the term actually queried). Optionally append a footnote: "queried as 'universal wire' per contemporaneous naming; see World Wire rename note above." |

## 3. Important Issues

| File | Issue | Fix |
|---|---|---|
